title: The House with the Twisting Passage
creator: Marion St. John Webb
description: LibriVox recording of The House with the Twisting Passage, by Marion St. John Webb. Read by Xenutia.] When Jenny goes to stay with her Aunt Abby, a caretaker in a grand old manor-house, she discovers a wonderful twisting passage on the second floor with an array of colourful characters living in the rooms along it – each of them with a story to tell. (Summary by Xenutia) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: LibriVox;Audiobook;Children
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: The only reason I give this story a 4 is that the stories within the story did not always seem to flow together as well as I thought they could have.  It is a sweet book though and quite appropriate for children.  The narrator was wonderful and her charming accent made my journeys to and fro to work a wonderful escape.  I would love to hear this narrator again.

Thanks to this excellent reader for keeping me company on a long car ride. The reader has a nice voice and good delivery. The story kept my attention but didn't require a lot of concentration. (Which is good in the car)

5 stars for the reader, 4 for the story.
